      • doc

      • sentence

        private edu.stanford.nlp.simple.Sentence sentence
        The reason we also provide a Sentence is because even though this and the Document will have the same text, Stanford's OpenNLP treats a Document and a Sentence differently semantically. That should make sense since the context of a super long Sentence is very different than the culminating context of all of its sub sentences. Thus, running the same annotations on a Document and Sentence produces different results. Instead of choosing between one, we will just compile them together.
